===GRIDSTRAL_OPERATOR_ENVELOPE_JSON===
{
  "envelope_version": "gridstral.operator.v1",
  "intent": "execute_feedback_cycle",
  "trace_id": "echoes-kbase-2026-05",
  "mission_one_liner": "Turn Gridstral's prior recommendations into bounded autonomous execution with auditable outputs.",
  "fork_choice": {
    "type": "explicit_pick_required",
    "options": [
      {
        "id": "path_a_validation_contract",
        "title": "Contract-safe vector↔metadata reconciliation",
        "objective": "Define and emit a schema-valid validation_report artifact that compares vector index lineage to SQLite sidecar rows with drift and confidence thresholds.",
        "must_emit": [
          {
            "artifact_type": "validation_report",
            "mime_hints": ["application/json", "text/markdown"],
            "required_sections": ["inputs_digest", "matched_pairs", "orphans_vectors", "orphans_sqlite", "threshold_results", "recommended_actions"]
          }
        ],
        "dry_run_first": true,
        "fail_closed": true
      },
      {
        "id": "path_b_audit_decision_log",
        "title": "Autonomy guardrail demo",
        "objective": "Produce a minimal integration spec and sample NDJSON event line for logging agent decisions to an operator-visible audit sink.",
        "must_emit": [
          {
            "artifact_type": "decision_log_contract",
            "required_fields": ["ts_iso8601", "decision_id", "decision_title", "decision_text", "rationale", "affected_criteria", "confidence", "dry_run"],
            "example_ndjson_line": "single canonical example"
          }
        ],
        "dry_run_first": false,
        "fail_closed": true
      }
    ]
  },
  "autonomy_policy": {
    "mode": "bounded",
    "allowed_without_human": ["draft_specs", "produce_diffs", "emit_validation_reports_dry_run", "enumerate_files_under_repo_root_relative_paths_only"],
    "requires_human_before_write": ["apply_sql_migration", "modify_production_cron", "rotate_keys", "sudo", "network_exfil", "delete_operator_data"],
    "stop_conditions": [
      {"when": "ambiguous_fork", "behavior": "halt_and_emit_QUESTIONS_JSON_only"},
      {"when": "threshold_violation", "behavior": "quarantine_event_stub_no_live_fix"}
    ]
  },
  "acceptance_gates": [
    {"gate": "machine_parseable_output", "rule": "Final assistant message MUST contain a second fenced block titled OPERATOR_RESULT_JSON with parseable JSON matching trigger.one_of_results_schema"},
    {"gate": "no_placeholder_TODOs", "rule": "No TODO or mock-tool stubs in emitted artifacts"},
    {"gate": "plain_operator_summary", "rule": "Include ≤ 12 bullet operator summary in plain English after the JSON block"}
  ],
  "one_of_results_schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "required": ["chosen_path_id", "status", "artifacts", "next_human_touchpoints"],
    "properties": {
      "chosen_path_id": {"enum": ["path_a_validation_contract", "path_b_audit_decision_log", "blocked_ambiguous"]},
      "status": {"enum": ["completed", "blocked", "dry_run_only_completed"]},
      "artifacts": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "object", "required": ["artifact_type", "body_markdown_or_json"]}},
      "next_human_touchpoints": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}}
    }
  }
}
===END_OPERATOR_ENVELOPE===

You previously answered our Echoes/personal-rag thread with two forks (validation contract vs auditable decision logging). That answer is now treated as **accepted guidance**, not theory.

**Triggering mandate (execute now)**
1. Pick **exactly one** fork (`path_a_validation_contract` OR `path_b_audit_decision_log`). If you truly cannot pick without one binary clarification, emit `chosen_path_id: blocked_ambiguous` plus **one** blocking yes/no question **inside** `OPERATOR_RESULT_JSON` only.
2. Produce **real artifacts**: markdown specs, JSON schemas, concrete thresholds, and runnable pseudo-cli commands scoped to a repo-relative layout (`kbase/`, `ops/`, `examples/` style)—nothing generic.
3. End with the mandatory **`OPERATOR_RESULT_JSON`** fenced block consumed by automation.

Autonomous posture is allowed **inside** the autonomy_policy.allow_without_human list only; otherwise refuse and log rationale.

Begin.
